result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI 6th [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI 6th [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Clifford Edward Tyler was found guilty of OWI 6th [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
